<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1117,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, M. R." box="[446,616,1118,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="288" pagination="208 - 213" refId="ref3753" refString="Wheeler, M. R. (1960) A new genus and two new species of Neotropical flies (Diptera: Drosophilidae). Entomological News, 71 (8), 208 - 213." type="journal article" year="1960">Wheeler, 1960</bibRefCitation>
). Frons and face extremely narrow, slightly more than the width of the lateral ocelli; margins parallel, with few minute setulae; anterior fronto-orbital bristle smaller, 
<emphasis box="[1224,1250,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">ca</emphasis>
. half the size of other bristles on frons; all bristles, setae, and setulae yellow; lacking propleural bristle; ocellar setae very small, cruciate; postvertical setae small, 
<emphasis box="[542,568,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">ca</emphasis>
. three times smaller than the inner vertical bristle; wing with dark pattern, encompassing crossveins dm–cu, bm–cu and distal half of cells r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[894,920,1280,1294]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">4+5</subScript>
, r 
<subScript attach="both" box="[945,970,1280,1294]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">2+3</subScript>
and r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1029,1037,1280,1294]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="288">1</subScript>
; abdomen yellow with black spots on tergites III, IV and V; epandrium complex with inverted U-shape, entirely covered with microtrichia; surstylus almost fused with epandrium, with peg-presinsetae; ventral lobe of epandrium pointed or round; distiphallus with upward projection; postgonites almost fused, without setae; hypandrium Y-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
